{"title_page": "Rape statistics", "text_new": "\n\n\n'''Statistics on rape''' and other [[sexual assault]]s are commonly available in industrialized countries, and are becoming more common throughout the world. Inconsistent [[Rape#Definitions|definitions of rape]], different rates of reporting, recording, prosecution and conviction for [[rape]] create controversial statistical disparities, and lead to accusations that many rape statistics are unreliable or misleading.<ref name=\"Gordon2002\">{{cite book|author=L. P. Gordon|title=Violence Against Women|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=rmXf-lSuqcgC|year=2002|publisher=Nova Publishers|isbn=978-1-59033-455-3|pages=[https://books.google.com/books?id=rmXf-lSuqcgC&pg=PA4 4\u20136]}}</ref><ref name=TCJ /> In some jurisdictions, male-female rape is the only form of rape counted in the statistics.<ref name=TCJ>{{cite web|url=http://www.cjonline.com/stories/080804/loc_crimestats.shtml |title=Statistics can be misleading |publisher=CJOnline.com |date=8 August 2004 |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref> Countries may not define forced sex on a spouse as \"rape\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youthkiawaaz.com/2014/05/forced-intercourse-marriage-rape-says-delhi-court-low-can-stoop/|title=Forced Intercourse In Marriage Not Rape, Says Delhi Court: How Low Can We Stoop? - Youth Ki Awaaz|date=12 May 2014}}</ref> Rape is a severely under-reported crime with surveys showing [[Dark figure of crime|dark figures]] of up to 91.6% of rapes going unreported.<ref>{{cite web|title=ITALIAN NATIONAL STATISTIC INSTITUTE (ISTAT) SURVEY ON VIOLENCE AGAINST WOMEN, 2006 |url=http://sgdatabase.unwomen.org/searchDetail.action?measureId=26309&baseHREF=country&baseHREFId=675 |website=unwomen.org |publisher=UN WOMEN |accessdate=26 August 2016 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140201182537/http://sgdatabase.unwomen.org/searchDetail.action?measureId=26309&baseHREF=country&baseHREFId=675 |archivedate=1 February 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Drug-facilitated, Incapacitated, and Forcible Rape: A National Study|journal=NCJRS|date=February 2007|pages=70|url=https://www.ncjrs.gov/app/publications/abstract.aspx?ID=240972|accessdate=26 August 2016}}</ref> >\n\nA [[United Nations]] statistical report compiled from government sources showed that more than 250,000 cases of rape or attempted rape were recorded by police annually. The reported data covered 65 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unodc.org/unodc/en/data-and-analysis/Eighth-United-Nations-Survey-on-Crime-Trends-and-the-Operations-of-Criminal-Justice-Systems.html|title=Eighth United Nations Survey on Crime Trends and the Operations of Criminal Justice Systems |publisher=Unodc.org |date=31 March 2005 |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref>\n\n==Research==\n[[File:(A) Rape rates per 100000 population 2010-2012, world.jpg|thumb|280px|Reported Rape rates per 100,000 population 2010\u20132012.|alt=]]\n[[File:Listening to girls in Zambia (8220719638).jpg|thumb|In a recent survey of schoolgirls in [[Lusaka]], [[Zambia]], 53% reported that girls in their school have experienced sexual harassment.]]\nMost rape research and reporting to date has been limited to male-female forms of rape. Research on male-male and female-male is beginning to be done. However, almost no research has been done on [[Lesbian rape|female-female rape]], though women can be charged with rape in a few jurisdictions. A few books, such as ''Violent Betrayal: Partner Abuse in Lesbian Relationships'' by Dr. Claire M. Renzetti,<ref>Renzetti, Claire M. ''[https://archive.org/details/violentbetrayalp00renz Violent Betrayal: Partner Abuse in Lesbian Relationships]''. Thousand Oaks, CA: Sage Publications, 1992, {{ISBN|0-8039-3888-8}}.</ref> ''No More Secrets: Violence in Lesbian Relationships'' by Janice Ristock,<ref>Ristock, Janice. ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=s00oU23jgPMC&dq=No+More+Secrets:+Violence+in+Lesbian+Relationships&source=bl&ots=UyatauXB9f&sig=b_Vthc4r6fseoM1fM6innbZwhic&hl=en&sa=X&ei=91YZUJ-qIeLW0QWC6oHYDw&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAA No More Secrets: Violence in Lesbian Relationships]''. New York: Routledge, 2002, {{ISBN|0-415-92946-6}}.</ref> and ''Woman-to-Woman Sexual Violence: Does She Call It Rape?'' by Lori B. Girshick<ref>Girshick, Lori B. ''[https://books.google.com/books/about/Woman_To_Woman_Sexual_Violence.html?id=nHg40DDZWjAC&redir_esc=y Woman-to-Woman Sexual Violence: Does She Call It Rape?] (The Northeastern Series on Gender, Crime, and the Law)''. Boston: Northeastern University Press, 2000, {{ISBN|1-55553-527-5}}.</ref> also cover the topic of rape of women by other women.\n\n==By country==\nThis table indicates the number of, and per capita cases of recorded rape by country. It does not, and of course cannot, include cases of rape which go unreported or unrecorded.<ref name=autogenerated1 /><ref name=undata>{{cite web|url=http://www.unodc.org/documents/data-and-analysis/statistics/crime/CTS12_Sexual_violence.xls |title=Statistics : Crime : Sexual Violence (see second tab of spreadsheet) |publisher=Unodc.org |accessdate=2013-12-04}}</ref> It does not specify whether recorded means reported, brought to trial, or convicted. Each entry is based on that country's definition of rape, which varies widely throughout the world. The list does not include the estimated rape statistics of the countries, per year, such as [[South Africa]] having 500,000 rapes per year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irinnews.org/report/84909/south-africa-one-in-four-men-rape |title=SOUTH AFRICA: One in four men rape |publisher=Irinnews.org |date=18 June 2009 |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref> [[China]] having 31,833 rapes a year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uschina.usc.edu/w_usci/showarticle.aspx?articleID=13037&AspxAutoDetectCookieSupport=1 |title=Rape in China, University of Southern California (May 7, 2009) |publisher=Uschina.usc.edu |accessdate=2013-12-03}}</ref> [[Rape in Egypt|Egypt]] having more than 200,000 rapes a year,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.escapeartistes.com/2012/04/26/how-safe-is-egypt-after-the-revolution/ |title=How Safe is Egypt After the Revolution? Updated 20 June |publisher=Escapeartistes.com |accessdate=2013-12-04|date=26 April 2012 }}</ref> and the United Kingdom at 85,000 rapes a year.<ref name=\"easton1\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"page-break-before:always;\"\n|+ Rape at the national level, number of police-recorded offences<ref name=undata />{{Additional citation needed|date=January 2019|reason=Some of the countries in the table are not in the source}}\n|-\n!\n! colspan=\"8\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | '''Total count'''\n! colspan=\"8\" style=\"text-align: center;\" | '''Rate per 100,000 population'''\n|-\n! '''Country/territory'''\n! 2003\n! 2004\n! 2005\n! 2006\n! 2007\n! 2008\n! 2009\n! 2010\n! 2003\n! 2004\n! 2005\n! 2006\n! 2007\n! 2008\n! 2009\n! 2010\n\n|-\n| Kenya||||1440||1365||1291||876||735||847||||||4.1||3.8||3.5||2.3||1.9||2.1||\n|-\n| Mauritius||53||40||38||64||77||69||57||51||4.3||3.2||3.0||5.1||6.0||5.4||4.4||3.9\n|-\n| Mozambique||||102||64||46||41||47||44||||||0.5||0.3||0.2||0.2||0.2||0.2||\n|-\n| Uganda||0||549||732||750||599||1536||619||709||2.0||2.0||2.6||2.6||2.0||4.9||1.9||2.1\n|-\n| Zimbabwe||3858||4997||4790||4967||4762||3186||||||30.6||39.7||38.1||39.6||38.2||25.6||||\n|-\n| Cameroon||451||555||592||580||447||||||||2.7||3.2||3.4||3.2||2.4||||||\n|-\n| Algeria||723||630||376||495||836||812||||||2.3||1.9||1.1||1.5||2.5||2.4||||\n|-\n| Morocco||618||453||475||1063||1215||1130||1507||||2.1||1.5||1.6||3.5||3.9||3.6||4.8||\n|-\n| Sudan||||||||||||1189||||||||||||||||2.9||||\n|-\n| Botswana||||||||||||||1754||1865||||||||||||||88.5||92.9\n|-\n| Lesotho||||||||||1797||1878||1777||||||||||||85.3||88.3||82.7||\n|-\n| Swaziland||785||849||||||||||||||72.1||77.5||||||||||||\n|-\n| Guinea||||||||||92||||||||||||||||1.0||||||\n|-\n| Senegal||||||301||159||167||416||710||693||||||2.8||1.4||1.5||3.5||5.9||5.6\n|-\n| Sierra Leone||||||||||135||79|||||